<plot>Cleanflix follows the sanitized movie industry from inception to collapse. Starting with Kate Winslet's bare breasts in Titanic and the Mormon culture that didn't want to see them, the film launches into the numerous legal and theoretical debates that led to a DGA lawsuit involving industry titans like Martin Scorsese, Steven Soderbergh, Steven Spielberg, and Robert Redford. And that's only the beginning. The film then tracks the dozen or so stores that defied court order and remained in operation, focusing on the infamous Daniel Thompson, de facto leader of Utah's the edited movie revival.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?108431</url></doc>
